## Models Evaluated (ranked by overall GeoCrossBench score)

1. **Ï‡ViT** (44.51) â€” best cross-band generalization, ChannelViT + iBOT, pretrained on 23M images
2. **DINOv3** (42.88) â€” general-purpose, competitive in-distribution
3. **iBOT** (42.32) â€” best in-distribution (64.73 RGB)
4. **ViT-B** (41.22) â€” ImageNet pretrained baseline
5. **DINOv2** (41.16) â€” best in-distribution average (63.89)
6-24. DOFA, TerraFM, SatlasNet, CROMA, Prithvi, AnySat, ResNet50 (all weaker)

Key finding: RS-specific models do NOT outperform general-purpose models in-distribution. Ï‡ViT wins only in cross-band scenarios due to channel-wise tokenization + hierarchical channel sampling during pretraining.

