## Superset Setup & Metrics (Paper Analysis)

### Superset Definition
Test-time inputs have **strictly more bands** than training. Simulates legacy models operating on newer sensors with additional bands.

### Superset Configurations

| Train on | Evaluate on | Description |
|----------|-------------|-------------|
| RGB | RGBN | 3-band optical â†’ 4-band (adds NIR, S2 B8) |
| S2 | S2+S1 | 10-band multispectral â†’ 12-band optical+SAR (adds VV, VH) |

### Superset Finding
Models degrade **5â€“25%** on average when given additional bands at test time. Architectures overfit to input channel count/distribution and fail to integrate novel spectral information without fine-tuning.

### Superset Rankings (full fine-tuning)

| Rank | Model | RGB | S2 | RGBâ†’RGBN | S2â†’S2+S1 | Superset AVG |
|------|-------|-----|-----|----------|----------|--------------|
| 1 | Ï‡ViT | 61.81 | 63.53 | 59.03 | 57.96 | 58.49 |
| 2 | DINOv3 | 62.46 | 63.0 | 52.48 | 59.62 | 56.05 |
| 3 | iBOT | 64.73 | 61.73 | 52.36 | 57.04 | 54.70 |
| 4 | ViT-B | 62.77 | 62.72 | 46.03 | 58.23 | 52.13 |
| 5 | DINOv2 | 65.26 | 62.53 | 54.52 | 47.59 | 51.06 |

DINOv3 strong on S2â†’S2+S1 (59.62) but weaker on RGBâ†’RGBN (52.48). DINOv2 opposite. Ï‡ViT best on both. AnySat/Prithvi worst in superset.

